        "description": "The choice of turbulence closure (e.g. SST k-omega) and hemolysis power-law model must be justified through comparison of at least two candidate models, with the selected model demonstrating superior agreement with experimental data."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected over realizable k-epsilon based on superior NIH prediction accuracy (mean absolute error 7.1% vs 14.3%). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model compared against Arora model; Giersiepen selected based on lower bias at high-shear operating points. Model form selection documented. Level 4 met."
